    "narrative": "For the April 26th slate, the Austin Waves lineup is anchored by two high-upside plays in the outfield: **Luis Robert Jr.** (76.49) and **Kyle Tucker** (74.75). **Luis Robert Jr.** benefits from a favorable matchup against Quintana, where dynamic platoon splits provide a +14% boost despite a slight headwind. Meanwhile, **Kyle Tucker** remains an elite start against Imanaga; while the lefty matchup typically suppresses production, the projected wind out conditions and strong individual skill metrics bolster his outlook significantly. **Jackson Merrill** (68.06) and **Josh Lowe** (66.42) also project as essential contributors, with **Josh Lowe** offering elite stolen base potential\u2014a critical priority for our roster construction\u2014provided he navigates the 45% rain risk in his matchup against Lugo.\n\nThe decision to keep **Gunnar Henderson** (52.11) on the bench was the most difficult call of the morning. While he remains a core part of our long-term strategy, his score was suppressed by a matchup against Early\u2019s elite 2.34 xERA and unfavorable platoon splits. The optimizer prioritized the more favorable individual matchups for starters like **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (63.82) and **Andy Pages** (59.94), the latter of whom earns a boost from projected wind conditions at the park. We are closely monitoring the lineup status for **Liam Hicks**, **Kyle Tucker**, **Andy Pages**, **Jackson Merrill**, **Josh Lowe**, and **Nolan Schanuel**; should any of these players fail to appear in their projected spots, we will pivot to ensure we are maximizing our daily game caps. **Josh Lowe** and **Nolan Schanuel** carry the highest volatility today due to the aforementioned weather concerns, but given their profiles, they remain the optimal play over our current bench options like **Marcell Ozuna** and **Coby Mayo**.",
